83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
House Bill 4052
Sponsored by Representative RESCHKE; Representative SCHARF, Senators DRAZAN, SMITH DB (Presession filed.)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: The Act makes a new tax credit for new banks. (Flesch Readability Score: 100.0).
Creates a corporate excise tax credit for each of the first three years that a bank does business
in this state.
Applies only to Oregon-chartered banks that commence business in tax years beginning on or
after January 1, 2027, and before January 1, 2033.
Takes effect on the 91st day following adjournment sine die.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to a tax credit for de novo banks; creating new provisions; amending ORS 314.772 and
3 318.031; and prescribing an effective date.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. Section 2 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part of ORS chapter 317.
6 SECTION 2. (1) As used in this section:
7 (a) “De novo bank” means a depository institution, as defined in 12 U.S.C. 1813(c), that:
8 (A) Was first issued a charter or certificate of authority to conduct banking business and
9 commenced business in this state during the current tax year or in either of the two im-
10 mediately preceding tax years; and
11 (B) Is chartered in Oregon.
12 (b) “De novo bank” does not include a bank that is formed by, merged with or converted
13 by a taxpayer that has filed a return under this chapter in any preceding tax year.
14 (2) A credit against taxes that are otherwise due under this chapter is allowed to a tax-
15 payer that is a de novo bank.
16 (3) The credit allowed under this section shall be computed by determining the amount
17 of tax that would otherwise be imposed on a de novo bank under this chapter, but may not
18 exceed $1 million in each of three consecutive tax years, beginning with the tax year in which
19 the de novo bank commences business in this state.
20 (4) Prior to claiming the credit allowed under this section, a taxpayer is required to
21 demonstrate having obtained, from the Director of the Department of Consumer and Busi-
22 ness Services, a bank charter under ORS chapter 707 and a certificate of authority to con-
23 duct banking business in this state.
24 (5) The credit allowed under this section may not exceed the tax liability of the taxpayer
25 for the tax year.
26 (6) Any tax credit otherwise allowable under this section that is not used by the taxpayer
27 in a particular tax year may be carried forward and offset against the taxpayer’s tax liability
28 for the next succeeding tax year. Any credit remaining unused in the next succeeding tax
